%N A183633 Number of (n+1) X (n+1) 0..3 arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 6.
%H A183633 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A183633/b183633.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A183633 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183633/a183633.txt">Proof of formula</a>, Jun 19 2026
%H A183633 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (11,-36,36).
%F A183633 a(n) = 4*(2^n-1)*3^(n+1)+4*2^n = 12*6^n-12*3^n+4*2^n. - _Zhuorui He_, Jun 13 2026
%F A183633 From _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 21 2026: (Start)
%F A183633 G.f.: 4*x*(11 - 36*x + 36*x^2)/((1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 6*x)).
%F A183633 E.g.f.: 4*(3*exp(6*x) - 3*exp(3*x) + exp(2*x) - 1). (End)
%e A183633 Some solutions for 3 X 3:
%e A183633 ..1..1..0....0..2..0....2..2..2....3..1..0....1..1..1....2..0..2....1..3..1
%e A183633 ..1..3..2....1..3..1....1..1..1....0..2..3....2..2..2....3..1..3....0..2..0
%e A183633 ..1..1..0....2..0..2....3..1..3....3..1..0....2..0..2....0..2..0....1..3..1
%t A183633 A183633[n_] := 12*6^n - 12*3^n + 4*2^n;
%t A183633 Array[A183633, 25] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Jun 22 2026 *)
